## Proof
Let \( n \) be a natural number. The two successive natural numbers are \( n \) and \( n+1 \). We consider the product \( n(n+1) \).

There are two cases to consider:
1. If \( n \) is even, then \( n = 2k \) for some integer \( k \). Hence,
