   \[
   n(n+1) = (2k+1) \cdot 2(k+1) = 2 \times (2k^2 + 3k + 1),
   \]
   which is also even because it is divisible by 2.

In either case, the product \( n(n+1) \) is even. Therefore, the product of any two successive natural numbers is even.

